cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with 3D object reconstruction from images, which is a task commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves leveraging the geometric structure of graph-encoded objects, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.GR). The paper also introduces a new training objective and heuristic for adaptive mesh generation, which could be considered machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) topics. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the ShapeNet dataset, which is commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) research for generating textual descriptions of 3D objects.
